JavaScript follows sequential execution, meaning it runs code line by line from top to bottom.

Each instruction completes before the next one starts, so the written order controls the output order.

In real projects, understanding this helps in debugging and predicting behavior.

Example:
console.log(1);
console.log(2);

Use declaration with let to create the variable without assigning a value.

This creates the container first and allows assigning a value later when needed.

This approach is common when values are received from user input or API responses.

Example:
let age;
